<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1437,615,963]" lastBlockId="2.[151,775,1299,1972]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Description. Male. Wing 2.0 mm long, 
<quantity box="[1299,1379,615,639]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
wide (N=2). Color: light and dark-banded flagellomeres (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="1.[151,188,1927,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,996,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-6. Male of Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002: 1, head (frontal view); 2, third flagelomere; 3, palpus; 4, wing; 5, first tarsomere; 6, tarsal claw and empodium" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558257/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) and legs; thorax brown; wing veins covered with dark brown scales and setae, wing membrane hyaline; legs and abdomen covered with dark brown scales and setae, tergites and sternites brown, non-sclerotized areas orange. Head (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="1.[151,188,1927,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,996,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-6. Male of Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002: 1, head (frontal view); 2, third flagelomere; 3, palpus; 4, wing; 5, first tarsomere; 6, tarsal claw and empodium" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558257/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Eye holoptic, facets hexagonal, closely adjacent, eye bridge 9 facets long, occiput brown with long hairs; occipital protuberance absent. Antenna with scape rectangular, pedicel rounded, 12 flagellomeres, cylindrical, necks bare; all approximately the same length, light basally and dark distally; circumfila sinuous (
<figureCitation box="[469,538,1299,1323]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="1.[151,188,1927,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,996,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-6. Male of Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002: 1, head (frontal view); 2, third flagelomere; 3, palpus; 4, wing; 5, first tarsomere; 6, tarsal claw and empodium" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeus with 19 setae; labella hemispherical in frontal view, completely setose distally; palpus 4-segmented, first and second segments equally long, third longer, fourth longest, all cylindrical, setae number and position as in 
<figureCitation box="[493,586,1429,1453]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="1.[151,188,1927,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,996,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-6. Male of Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002: 1, head (frontal view); 2, third flagelomere; 3, palpus; 4, wing; 5, first tarsomere; 6, tarsal claw and empodium" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figure 3</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
