<paragraph blockId="2.[151,775,1299,1972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Thorax. Wing blade hyaline, veins covered with scales and setae (
<figureCitation box="[325,388,1494,1518]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="1.[151,188,1927,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,996,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-6. Male of Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002: 1, head (frontal view); 2, third flagelomere; 3, palpus; 4, wing; 5, first tarsomere; 6, tarsal claw and empodium" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Antepronotal lobe bare. Scutum and scutelum dark brown, completely fused, scutum with three rows of dorsocentral setae, scutelum with row of macrosetae, anepistern with 40 setae, anepimeron with 19 macrosetae, katepistern and mediotergite bare; laterotergites with two trichoid sensila at halter base. Legs with first tarsomere without apicoventral spur (
<figureCitation box="[336,395,1688,1712]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="1.[151,188,1927,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,996,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-6. Male of Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002: 1, head (frontal view); 2, third flagelomere; 3, palpus; 4, wing; 5, first tarsomere; 6, tarsal claw and empodium" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); tarsal claws without tooth in all legs, bent beyond midway apex, empodia as long as claws (
<figureCitation box="[700,762,1721,1745]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="1.[151,188,1927,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,996,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-6. Male of Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002: 1, head (frontal view); 2, third flagelomere; 3, palpus; 4, wing; 5, first tarsomere; 6, tarsal claw and empodium" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,775,1299,1972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Abdomen. Tergites and sternites rectangular except for tergite 8 that is narrow; tergites and sclerites 2–7 with posterior line of strong setae, completely covered with scales, and a pair of trichoid sensilla anteriorly (except for sternite 2).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,775,1299,1972]" lastBlockId="2.[813,1437,1299,1973]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[353,416,1883,1907]" captionStart="Fig 7" captionStartId="2.[151,179,1189,1208]" captionTargetBox="[228,1280,198,1101]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,151,1182]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig 7. Male of Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002. Terminalia ventral view, left and dorsal view, right (ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostyle; hy, hypoproct; pa, paramere)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558259/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites oblong, completely covered with setae and microsetae, with large ventro-apical lobe exceeding insertion of gonostylus; gonostylus inserted dorsally, gonostylus rectangular with a projection in ventral portion of apex and a dorso-apical row of strong spines partially fused at base in dorsal portion of apex; cerci as long as hypoproct; hypoproct bilobed, narrow, setose, shorter than aedeagus; parameres short, round, setose; aedeagus narrow-triangular, strongly sclerotized, tapering gradually toward apex, round at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[813,1437,1299,1973]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Complementary description of pupa (
<figureCitation box="[1269,1359,1526,1550]" captionStart="Figs 8-11" captionStartId="3.[151,188,1212,1231]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,156,1181]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,132,1197]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 8-11. Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002. Figs 8, 9, pupa: 8, cephalic region (ventral view); 9, posterior region (dorsal view); Figs.10, 11, larva: 10, prothoracic spatula and lateral papillae (ventral view); 11, terminal segment (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558261/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
). Color orange. Body 
<quantity box="[959,1038,1559,1583]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
long (N=3). Cephalic region with pair of setae; antennal horns absent, upper and lower frontal horns absent, one pair of lower facial papillae with long setae, three pairs of lateral papillae (one setose and two bare); prothoracic spiracle long, setiform. Abdominal tergites 2–7 with field of strong simple spines, concentrated in discal area of tergites; terminal segment with two rounded lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[813,1437,1299,1973]" lastBlockId="3.[151,776,1341,1973]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Larva (
<figureCitation box="[969,1099,1786,1810]" captionStart="Figs 8-11" captionStartId="3.[151,188,1212,1231]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,156,1181]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,132,1197]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 8-11. Schizomyia tuiuiu Urso-Guimarães &amp; Amorim, 2002. Figs 8, 9, pupa: 8, cephalic region (ventral view); 9, posterior region (dorsal view); Figs.10, 11, larva: 10, prothoracic spatula and lateral papillae (ventral view); 11, terminal segment (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558261/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 10, 11</figureCitation>
). Color white, body elongate, cylindrical, tapered anteriorly, broadly rounded posteriorly. Integument smooth. Spatula with pair of pointy anterior lobes and long shaft posteriorly. Lateral papillae in two triplets on each side of spatula, each triplet with two setose papillae and 1 asetose papilla. Eighth abdominal segment with a mediodorsal lobe discrete on posterior margin; terminal segment with four pairs of papillae, three corniform and one with a long setae.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3558261" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3558261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3558261/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" startId="3.[151,188,1212,1231]" subCaptionStartIDs="3.[713,750,1212,1231] 3.[151,192,1237,1256]" subCaptionStarts="Figs 8 &amp; Figs.10" targetBox="[200,1388,156,1181]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1211,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
